## 📦 Required Software and Tools

This is the core toolkit for our bootcamp. Each tool plays a vital role in the modern web development workflow.

### 1️⃣ Visual Studio Code (VS Code)
<p>
  <img align="left" src="https://img.icons8.com/fluency/48/000000/visual-studio-code-2019.png" alt="VS Code" width="40" style="margin-right: 15px;"/>
  <b>Purpose:</b> Our primary, lightweight, and highly extensible source code editor.
</p>
<br/>

🔗 **Download:** [https://code.visualstudio.com/](https://code.visualstudio.com/)

> **🌟 Pro Tip:** Once installed, explore the Extensions Marketplace (Ctrl+Shift+X). A well-configured editor is your best friend!

---
### 2️⃣ Node.js (LTS Version)
<p>
  <img align="left" src="https://img.icons8.com/color/48/000000/nodejs.png" alt="Node.js" width="40" style="margin-right: 15px;"/>
  <b>Purpose:</b> The JavaScript runtime environment that allows us to run JavaScript on the server. Installing Node.js also installs <code>npm</code> (Node Package Manager), which we will use constantly.
</p>
<br/>

🔗 **Download:** [https://nodejs.org/en/download](https://nodejs.org/en/download)

> **⚠️ Important:** Always download the **LTS (Long-Term Support)** version for maximum stability and compatibility.

---
### 3️⃣ Git
<p>
  <img align="left" src="https://img.icons8.com/color/48/000000/git.png" alt="Git" width="40" style="margin-right: 15px;"/>
  <b>Purpose:</b> The industry-standard distributed version control system. It's the safety net for our code, enabling collaboration and tracking every change.
</p>
<br/>

🔗 **Download:** [https://git-scm.com/downloads](https://git-scm.com/downloads)

---
### 4️⃣ GitHub Account
<p>
  <img align="left" src="https://img.icons8.com/material-outlined/48/000000/github.png" alt="GitHub" width="40" style="margin-right: 15px;"/>
  <b>Purpose:</b> The world's largest code hosting and collaboration platform. This is where your portfolio will live and where you will submit your bootcamp projects.
</p>
<br/>

🔗 **Create Account:** [https://github.com/](https://github.com/)

> **💡 Action Item:** After creating your account, bookmark your profile page. This will become your professional developer resume.

---
### 5️⃣ MongoDB Community Server
<p>
  <img align="left" src="https://img.icons8.com/color/48/000000/mongodb.png" alt="MongoDB" width="40" style="margin-right: 15px;"/>
  <b>Purpose:</b> The "M" in MERN. A powerful NoSQL database that stores data in flexible, JSON-like documents, making it a perfect match for JavaScript development.
</p>
<br/>

🔗 **Download:** [https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community](https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community)

> **🛠️ Installation Guidance:**
> - **Windows:** It's recommended to install MongoDB as a Windows Service for automatic startup. The installer wizard will guide you through this.
> - **macOS/Linux:** Follow the platform-specific instructions carefully. On macOS, using `brew` (`brew install mongodb-community`) is a popular and clean method.

---
### 6️⃣ MongoDB Compass
<p>
  <img align="left" src="https://img.icons8.com/color/48/000000/mongodb.png" alt="Compass" width="40" style="margin-right: 15px;"/>
  <b>Purpose:</b> The official graphical user interface (GUI) for MongoDB. It allows you to visually explore your data, build queries, and run aggregations without writing command-line code.
</p>
<br/>

🔗 **Download:** [https://www.mongodb.com/products/tools/compass](https://www.mongodb.com/products/tools/compass)

---
### 7️⃣ Postman
<p>
  <img align="left" src="https://img.icons8.com/dusk/64/000000/postman-api.png" alt="Postman" width="40" style="margin-right: 15px;"/>
  <b>Purpose:</b> The leading API development and testing tool. We'll use it to design, mock, debug, and test the REST APIs we build with Express.js.
</p>
<br/>

🔗 **Download:** [https://www.postman.com/downloads/](https://www.postman.com/downloads/)

---
### 8️⃣ Google Chrome
<p>
  <img align="left" src="https://img.icons8.com/color/48/000000/chrome--v1.png" alt="Chrome" width="40" style="margin-right: 15px;"/>
  <b>Purpose:</b> Our standard web browser for development and testing. Its industry-leading DevTools are indispensable for debugging front-end React code, inspecting network requests, and tuning performance.
</p>
<br/>

🔗 **Download:** [https://www.google.com/chrome/](https://www.google.com/chrome/)

